            'Some chemicals that have been in the news a lot lately are PFAS, which stands for Per- and Polyfluorinated Substances. They are potentially harmful and invisible to the naked eye. PFAS are chemicals used to make coatings that protect against heat, oil, stains, grease, and water for products in an array of industries. A number of industries have used PFAS since the early 1940s. \n',
